<dl id="n38143d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38143d">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38143d"> 143(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> shorttongue</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">We make, in fact, no pretence of speaking as we write; we use a form of shorthand, or <mark>short-tongue</mark> (as it should be called) <small> Sir Richard Paget, <a name="RPBP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RPBP"><cite title="source">Babel, or The Past, Present and Future of Human Speech</cite></a> (1930) 73</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
